****************************
Decide what happens when a successful location trigger is processed.
- Nothing. This will reset when you leave and return to the location.
- Disable. Turn off the location trigger.
- Reset. Will reevaluate as if you never entered or left the area.
- Delete. Remove the location trigger from Location Triggers.</string>

			<string>LimitKit allows you to control how often a shortcut can run its primary function. Learn more and download from:

https://tow.com/shortcuts/limitkit 

•••

Use LimitKit: Set to true to activate. 

Interval: The amount of time before the shortcut can run its primary function again. 

Unit values:

s - seconds
m - minutes
h - hours
d - days
w - weeks
mo - months
y - years</string>
